432        return (z = ((x = ((x = x * 0xC6BC279692B5CC85L + seed) ^ x >>> 26)
433                * ((y *= 0x9E3779B97F4A7C15L) ^ (y + 0x9E3779B97F4A7C15L))) ^ x >>> 28) * ((z *= 0x9E3779B97F4A7C15L) ^ z + 0x9E3779B97F4A7C15L)) ^ z >>> 28;

435    private double gradCoord2D(long seed, long x, long y, double xDiff, double yDiff) {
436        seed = hash2D(seed, x, y);
437        x = (seed >> 11);
438        y = (seed * 0xC13FA9A902A6328FL >> 11);
439        return
440                x * 0x1p-52 * (xDiff + (y * 0x6p-56)) +
441                        y * 0x1p-52 * (yDiff + (x * 0x6p-56));
442    }

723    private transient long[] scratch3;
724    private transient double[] scratch;
725    private transient int lastLen = -1;
726    private transient double lastEffect = 0x1.12bp-61;
727    public final double arbitraryNoise(long seed, double... coordinates) {
728        final int len = coordinates.length, upper = 1 << len;
729        final double effect;
730        if(len != lastLen)
731        {
732            lastLen = len;
733            lastEffect = effect = 0x1.81p-62 * Math.pow(1.1875, len);
734        }
735        else
736            effect = lastEffect;
737        if(scratch3 == null || scratch3.length < len * 3)
738            scratch3 = new long[len * 3];
739        if(scratch == null || scratch.length < upper)
740            scratch = new double[upper];
741        for (int i = 0; i < len; i++) {
742            seed = DiverRNG.determine(seed + 0xC6BC279692B5CC83L ^ ~seed << 32);
743            scratch3[i * 3 + 1] = (scratch3[i * 3] = (scratch3[i * 3 + 2] = longFloor(coordinates[i])) * seed) + seed;
744        }
745        long working;
746        for (int i = 0; i < upper; i++) {
747            working = 0L;
748            for (int j = 0; j < len; j++) {
749                working += scratch3[j * 3 + (i >> j & 1)];
750            }
751            scratch[i] = determine(working) * effect;
752        }
753        for (int i = 0; i < len; ++i) {
754            for (int j = 0, t = upper >> i; j < t; j += 2) {
755                scratch[j >> 1] = cerp(scratch[j], scratch[j + 1], coordinates[i] - scratch3[i * 3 + 2]);
756            }
757        }
758        return NumberTools.sway(scratch[0]);
759    }
